1 F. No person shall knowingly present any animal or therapy
2 animal as a service animal or intentionally misrepresent entitlement
3 to an animal in his or her possession as a qualified service animal
4 for the purpose of obtaining any of the rights or privileges set
5 forth in state or federal law for an individual with a disability.
6 Any person who violates this provision shall, upon conviction, be
7 guilty of a misdemeanor.
8 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
